                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01B11/11–2444</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-24">November 24,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ambassador Gromyko called this afternoon at his request.</p>
                <p>He stated that the purpose of his call was to take up again the question of the
                    deserter, Captain Kravchenko. He told me that he had submitted a communication
                    to Mr. Hull on the 6th of May on this subject and that he had never received an
                    answer and he felt it was now time to follow it up with a further request. He
                    then presented an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    <note n="32" xml:id="d1129fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> which was in Russian, and I assured the
                    Ambassador that the subject would receive the Department’s most prompt
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
